Right-to-Left Transaction Parsing

Each transaction row must be parsed from right to left, not from left to right.

Parsing order:

Read the amount field at the extreme right.
Remove the amount token from the transaction.
Extract the CONTO block by scanning right-to-left, collecting the account description words and the numeric account identifiers immediately preceding them.
Everything remaining before the CONTO block becomes DESCRIZIONE.
Extract N.Prot. (numeric). If missing, carry forward the previous non-empty value.
Extract N.RIF. (a single alphabetic character only, e.g., A, B, C). If missing, leave blank.
Extract DATA (dd/mm/yyyy). If missing, leave blank.

This right-to-left parsing order is a core requirement because the account (CONTO) and amount fields are consistently positioned at the end of each transaction, making them more reliable anchors than parsing from the left.
